# Member experience UI freeze

The logged-in member experience has reached production quality. **Do not redesign it.**

## Do not change (unless explicitly requested)

- Home, Discover, Chats, Signals, Profile, Settings
- Bottom navigation, header, card spacing, radius, typography, shadows
- Overall compact fintech feel (Moniepoint / Kuda / PalmPay / PiggyVest — not loud or amateur)

## Do not introduce

- Larger cards, buttons, or typography
- Loud banners, giant blocks, or unnecessary sections
- New spacing systems that diverge from existing tokens

## Allowed work (without visual redesign)

- Bug fixes
- Performance, security, stability
- Accessibility and responsive layout fixes (same visual language)
- Backend improvements

## New features

- Must inherit existing design tokens and spacing from `src/styles/member-fintech.css` and current member components
- No visual changes unless the user explicitly requests them
- Prefer surgical fixes over layout refactors

## Reference

Design tokens live in `.platform-root--member` (`--bs-*` variables). Reuse `member-fintech.css`, existing card patterns, and compact tap-select / form rows — do not invent parallel styles.
